\noun off
\color none

\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{O}^{n}$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}^{n}$
\end_inset

 is called the Borel 
\family default
\series default
\shape default
\size default
\emph default
\bar default
\strikeout default
\uuline default
\uwave default
\noun default
\color inherit

\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

-algebra, containing the Borel sets or Borel measurable sets and denoted
 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{B}\left(\mathbb{R}^{n}\right)$
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{B}^{n}$
\end_inset

.
 Sometimes this is also called the topological sigma algebra (because the
 open sets of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}^{n}$
\end_inset

 are also the basis sets of the standard topology on 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}^{n}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Theorem
If 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{O}^{n}$
\end_inset

,
\begin_inset Formula $C^{n}$
\end_inset

,
\begin_inset Formula $K^{n}$
\end_inset

 denote the families of open, closed, and compact sets in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}^{n}$
\end_inset

 then
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{B}\left(\mathbb{R}^{n}\right)=\sigma\left(\mathcal{O}^{n}\right)=\sigma\mbox{\ensuremath{\left(\mathcal{C}^{n}\right)}}=\sigma\left(\mathcal{K}^{n}\right)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Corollary
The 
\family roman
\series medium
\shape up
\size normal
\emph off
\bar no
\strikeout off
\uuline off
\uwave off
\noun off
\color none
Borel 
\family default
\series default
\shape default
\size default
\emph default
\bar default
\strikeout default
\uuline default
\uwave default
\noun default
\color inherit

\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

-algebra is also generated by any of the following systems
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\left\{ \left(-\infty,a\right):a\in\mathbb{Q}\right\}  & \left\{ \left(-\infty,a\right):a\in\mathbb{R}\right\} \\
\left\{ \left(a,\infty\right):a\in\mathbb{Q}\right\}  & \left\{ \left(a,\infty\right):a\in\mathbb{R}\right\} \\
\left\{ \left(-\infty,a\right]:a\in\mathbb{Q}\right\}  & \left\{ \left(-\infty,a\right]:a\in\mathbb{R}\right\} \\
\left\{ \left[a,\infty\right):a\in\mathbb{Q}\right\}  & \left\{ \left[a,\infty\right):a\in\mathbb{R}\right\} 
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

